"{\"uid\": \"blueprint.ng-whitlock-to-retire-after-paris-2024-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"April 11, 2024Admin IIISports0  Three-time Olympic gold medallist Max Whitlock will retire after the Paris 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 78, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Max Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 31-year-old, who has won 32 major international medals, is Britain's most successful gymnast.\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 183, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9830206699851738, \"rank\": 0.017266543737033117, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will become the first gymnast to win four Olympic medals on the same apparatus if he adds to his two golds and a bronze on the pommel horse this summer.\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This decision now feels right,\\\" Whitlock told BBC Breakfast.\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 409, \"end\": 417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.736819093216073e-35, \"text\": \"Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}, {\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Breakfast\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BBC Breakfast\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Breakfast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Breakfast\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Going for my final Olympic Games, it feels very, very strange talking about it and it's almost hard to articulate what it's like.\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a really nice mindset to be in, to think I will just give it all I have got.\\\"\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whitlock's Olympic journey started at London 2012, where he claimed bronze in the pommel horse and helped Great Britain finish third in the team event.\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.736819093216073e-35, \"text\": \"Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}, {\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999761258, \"rank\": 2.37733606583711e-11, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9911376692346564, \"rank\": 0.008940110402947536, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Rio 2016 he won bronze for Britain's first medal in the all-around event for 108 years, and became the nation's first individual Olympic gold medallist in artistic gymnastics with victory in the floor and pommel horse events.\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9830206699851738, \"rank\": 0.017266543737033117, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterretaining his pommel horse titleat the Tokyo Olympics in 2021, Whitlock took an18-month break from the sport to deal with mental health struggles.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1190, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.736819093216073e-35, \"text\": \"Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His other honours include three World Championship golds, four European Championship titles and four Commonwealth Games golds.\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Commonwealth_Games\", \"score\": 0.7073918928863917, \"rank\": 0.4134952072037098, \"text\": \"Commonwealth Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Commonwealth_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Commonwealth_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBA:\\u00a0Antetokounmpo exits Bucks-Celtics game with injury  World Rugby considers smaller ball for women  20212023 general electionsAFricaAPCAPC newsArmed forcesBanditsBenue stateBlueprintBoko HaramBuhariCourtcovid-19developmenteducationefccelectionFCT AbujaFeaturedFEDERAL GOVERNMENTFGINECinsecurityKaduna stateKano stateKogi stateLagos StateleadershipNigeria NewsNigerian NewsNigeria Police ForceOyo statePDP newsPolicePremier Leaguepresident muhammadupresident muhammadu buhariSecuritySenateSports NewsSuper Eaglesthe federal governmentTinubuUSzamfara state  Blue